latestIgtvVideos.title: MIND ( Original )
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Freedom is in your mind for the mind has infinite possibilities. Unexplored beauties and unexplainable emotions built on your experiences. You can be who you want to be, and feel what you want to feel and yet sometimes, our mind becomes the very shackles on our feet. And we are trapped in the mind that was supposed to be free
.
.
MIND is an imperfect track @oneirataxian.zg and I cooked up that's made on the essence of being stuck in the cage of your own mind. Being bound by the limits of your own vulnerability.
.
Please take out a minute and give it a listen and do share it if you like it❤ 
It would mean a lot to me
Headphones and full volume recommended

latestPosts.caption:
The language of music is eternal. One that connects through time , past prejudice and across cultures. Solely thread, by emotion and love. The language of expression and the sound of one's heart and soul. One that I am forever in awe of.

Grateful to be able to connect in my own little way to the larger workings of the music world vicariously through the lives of so many talented musicians.

Here are a few of my favourite excerpts from my conversations with these multifaceted artists, over the past year for @lifestyleasiaindia. 

Forever grateful to the team, who this wouldn't have been possible without.
 @rahulgangs_ @analitaseth @akshitanj @jhanvii.23 @mayuxkh

I could unfortunately only highlight 10 of them due to my un- upadated Instagram slide count, but take my word for it, the others i couldn't mention were just as noteworthy.

Read the full interviews at the link in my bio.

1. Sid Sriram on exploring the spectrum of his identity through music. (@sidsriram)
2. How Ankur Tewari is orchestrating a new generation of Indian music (@ankurtewari)
3. Osho Jain’s call for the Mountains (@oshojain_)
4. The Karan Kanchan Experience: In conversation with the multi-genre record producer (@karankanchanmusic)
5. People never change, but Peter Cat Recording Co. does (@petercatrecordingco)
6. Rock band Keane talks about staying relevant and a new age of creativity (@keaneofficial)
7. Hip-hop duo Seedhe Maut get candid about crossing borders with their sound (@seedhemaut)
8. Shilpa Rao on the changing nature of music (@shilparao)
9. Akshay & IP on forging a reimagined bridge between fashion and music (@akshayandip)
10.Pandit Ravi Shankar’s disciple, sitarist Rishab Rikhiram Sharma on the healing power of music (@rishabsmusic)

#Music #MusicJournalism #Interview #DHH #ClassicalMusic #Rock #BoyBand #IndieMusic #SidSriram #AnkurTewari #SeedheMaut #PeterCatRecordingCo #Keane #KaranKanchan

Watch the full interview on Lifestyle Asia India's YouTube Channel.

#TheTribe #CollabTribe #Interview #GroupInterview

I once read that doing something new each day is good for your mental wellness. Yet often, as we grow older we forget to do those new things and when we do- don't really take the time to look back and appreciate ourselves for doing it. It fills me with gratitude every time I'm able to do those new things, those firsts that I've always wanted to do. 

Got one of the most well known EDM artists across the globe on @lifestyleasiaindia 's October Cover, Interviewed him for my first cover story and also styled him for the shoot - a whole journey of firsts moulded into one excitingly hectic covershoot. Funny how life just seems to bring the things you love together with time, after all fashion, music and writing are all things I take very seriously - sometimes too much my friends would say. This one was a mix of all of the above, and I wouldn't have it any other way.

The point being - It fills me with gratitude to be able to live the life I want to, do the things I love doing, and keep growing everyday. And on days when they happen - those first are special. And it's not just the unseen hands of life, or your hard work that let's those things happen but also, the people around you. Deeply grateful to @rahulgangs_ for believing in me, @analitaseth for always, always pushing me to be better and being the backbone she's so good at being. @neelangana for trusting in me and my vision and letting me support hers in as much capacity as I'm able to. And of course @alanwalkermusic for making this possible. 

Here's presenting  @alanwalkermusic on the latest cover of @lifestyleasiaindia
